FASHION TIPS, TRICKS & MISTAKES

When I say fashion mistakes, I’m not talking about wearing an outfit that could land you on a worst-dressed list. 

I’m talking about long-held habits you refuse to break, fashion clichés you still believe are true, and small things you’re avoiding or doing that can destroy your personal style.

1. MONOCHROME MAKES YOU LOOK TALLER and SLIMMER
Monochrome outfit will instantly makes you look taller since it does not break up your silhouette at any point.

2. THE WRONG PANT LENGTH MAKES YOU LOOK SHORTER
The wrong pants can totally destroy your whole look and make you look shorter no matter how tall your heels are. 

3. YOU ALWAYS BUY THE SAME SIZE IN CLOTHES
Never look at the size, look at how the clothes fit you. Sizing can vary tremendously according to store, brand and item.

4. GO PREPARED
You are not likely to find the best outfits that you really want if you’re shopping in a hurry. You should set aside some time specifically for wardrobe shopping so that you can make sure the clothes you are buying are the right fit for you.

5. HIGH WAISTED BOTTOM IS ALWAYS FLATTERING
When worn correctly, they can trick the eye into thinking you’re taller and leaner by elongating your lower body. 

6. YOU NEVER GET ANYTHING TAILORED
This is undoubtedly one of the biggest fashion mistakes a person can make. Think about it: we’re all built differently, so mass-produced clothing won’t fit us all the same way. Having a tailor tweak hemlines, seams, sleeve lengths, even taking in too-wide garments can be the difference between looking fine and looking absolutely impeccable all the time.

7. CONQUER YOUR FEAR OF COLOR
To play it safe, combine a neutral with something bolder.  But think twice about pairing intense hues with black, which can look dated.

3 MAJOR REASONS WHY YOUR LOOKS MATTER 

While some people want to believe that looks don’t matter at all, the simple truth is that they DO. Perhaps in a perfect world people would only judge others based on the content of their character, but the truth is that CLOTHES and how one PRESENTS oneself is heavily IMPORTANT.

It can matter in PROFESSIONAL aspects of your life, ROMANTIC aspects, and much more. So if you are looking to IMPROVE your STATUS in LIFE in one way or another, chances are good that improving your style and clothes would absolutely help as well.

1. OUTFIT IMPACTS YOUR PERCEIVED STATUS
You might not want this to be true, but it simply is. Wearing GREAT CLOTHES is going to make people who you do not know THINK more HIGHLY of you. The reason why is because dressing well is something that people typically do when they are SUCCESSFUL and SERIOUS.

2. DRESSING WELL WILL HELP YOUR CONFIDENCE
Wearing great clothes is about more than HOW other PEOPLE PERCEIVE YOU. The fact of the matter is that wearing a WELL PUT TOGETHER OUTFIT is going to have just as big of an IMPACT on you as it does on the people you meet.

3. GREAT CLOTHES IMPROVE YOUR RESPONSIBILITY
As silly as it sounds, caring for your appearance will make you a more responsible person.  You wind up keeping track of details like which shoes need to be shined and which shirts need to be ironed, etc. 

Giving a damn about your appearance is a way of caring how much control you have over your own life - not just over what color of tie or dress to wear this morning.

PARTY OUTFIT FORMULA

We’ve officially entered the holiday season. It’s a well-known fact that picking the perfect party-season outfit can be tricky. 

This festive season is all about standing out - and more than a little bit of sparkle - so forget about being shy until after New Year’s.

These are my most favorite ideas for the holiday outfits when it comes to styling my clients. 

STATEMENT OUTWEAR
A chic coat or jacket might be an option. It’s the first thing people see, and you can use it to pull your entire look together.

SPARKLES
Incorporate a shimmering piece into your holiday look, whether it be a sequined skirt, a metallic blazer, or a cute, crystal-embellished pair of shoes. 

COLORS
Try to incorporate the season’s popular jewel tones into your outfit to help you get into the holiday spirit!

TEXTURES & LAYERS
Simplicity should be left to another season - during the holidays, your look should be festive and interesting. Leather, lace, real or faux fur, velvet, sheer rhinestone fabric, feathers, metallic fabrics or all-embellished-everything, give it a try!

VELVET SUITS
Velvet suits are that party staple. They’re not only ideal for more formal occasions (corporate holiday parties or weddings) but also can be tailored to your style with ease. 

EYE-CATCHING JEWELRY
Wear a gigantic necklace, or pull out the statement cocktail ring. Don’t be afraid to make a statement with your jewelry, just try to keep the rest of your look simple.

FASHION TIPS I ALWAYS SHARE WITH MY CLIENTS

It’s the end of the year and I’m sure everyone is already planning their next year - goals, intentions, actions, etc.As a stylist I highly recommend to include “CLOTHES AND HOW EVERYONE PRESENTS THEMSELVES ARE HEAVILY IMPORTANT” into that list.

People underestimate the power of fashion.But defining your style and developing a unique outfit is one of the most effective communication tools.
1. WORK YOUR BASE & CAPSULE WARDROBE.Make sure you have reliable wardrobe staples:an iconic little black dress, a pair of jeans that fit perfectly,a classic blazer, simple T-shirts and button-downs in neutral colors,an effortless leather jacket,denim jacket, etc.Investing in a capsule collection of mix-n-match basics(and learning how to style them) is the key to looking put together.
2. MAKE SURE YOUR CLOTHES FIT PERFECTLY.One trick to making any item of clothing look amazing is to hire a good stylist who’ll put everything together for you and a tailor.Tailored clothing not only looks polished, but it also feels more comfortable.Pants that drag on the ground and dresses that bunch up awkwardly won’t make you feel stylish.If your capsule wardrobe fits you well,you can start to play with over- and under-sized items in a way that feels fashionable,not sloppy.
3. LEARN HOW TO BALANCE PROPORTIONS.Balancing proportions is about styling your outfits to create an overall aesthetic harmony.The way you achieve this is by wearing clothes that are fitted to your body shape.Always pay attention to sleeve & pant/skirt length, shoulder & waist line.Because any small misbalance in proportions can make you look shorter,wider,and can change the look of your body type completely.
4. FIND YOUR PERSONAL STYLE.Developing a signature style can take years,but you can get started by creating a moodboard.Remember that personal style is an experiment.You never know what amazing looks await you until you’re in the fitting room.The categories “menswear” and “womenswear” shouldn’t dictate how you shop.Take time to play with colors and shapes to find what looks great on your unique body.

Happy New Year, my Instagram Family!❤️🎄🎉

HOW TO LAYER LIKE A PRO

Layering technique in styling is one of my favorite. Using more or fewer layers, or replacing one layer but not others, allows for flexible clothing to match the needs of each situation.

Layering also gives you the opportunity to play around with the pieces that are already in your wardrobe. Give yourself permission to experiment with different textures, fabrics, weights, patterns, and colors, and the outfit possibilities are endless.

COLOR IS KEY
Layering is best achieved when you keep your look to one or two color families - even down to the accessories. A print is ok, but keep it to one so that you don’t overwhelm your look.

FOCUS ON FABRICS
A nice mix of texture is essential for layering to keep the look interesting. Just be careful not to go too crazy, pick a few different fabric textures and weights and play around with them.

PLAY WITH PROPORTION
Proportion is everything when it comes to layering. The neck line and waist line, bottom length and shoe line (if we are talking about boots) - all these details are very important to have a right balance in your look.

STICK TO ONE BULKY ITEM
Any more than one big item and you’re venturing into unflattering territory. The key is to keep most of the layers on the lighter side and mix in one big piece.

Mastering the art of layering takes time and practice. Play around with different layered looks all the time until I find something that works. Creativity is key! There’s really no end to the number of combinations you can create and it’s a great way to get excited about your wardrobe again. And there’s no better way to stay warm this winter.

YOUR PERSONAL STYLE AS YOUR PERSONAL BRAND

What you wear is how you present yourself to the world, especially today, when human contacts are so quick. Fashion is an instant language.

Your personal brand reflects who you are, what you stand for, and what you do. Your personal style is a great way to express these things. So, why do people feel uncomfortable using fashion as a business tool? 

Even in this day and age, some people are still wrestling with the idea that being interested in fashion as a professional is frivolous (or even dangerous). 

WHY IT’S IMPORTANT TO STAND OUT WITH STYLE
Fashion is an extremely effective business tool in today’s marketplace. Having a fashion-forward appearance allows you to express your individuality through your style, allowing you to instantly communicate and reinforce your personal brand as a professional. 

Since your wardrobe is part of the packaging for your personal brand, learning how to dress according to your personal brand should be more than just an afterthought - it should be an intentional strategy to help you leave a memorable impression.

If you’re not sure where to start when it comes to what your personal brand actually is (or should be), ask yourself these two questions:
1. What do you want others to think about you, based on how you present yourself?
2. Does your current presentation of yourself align with how you want others to perceive you?

HOW TO ADD A POP OF COLOR TO ANY OUTFIT

A lot of the industry is trending towards neutrals and modern gray-scale. Because of this, adding color to your outfit can be a little intimidating for some people. Especially if you’re not used to styling your work to weekend wardrobes with bold hues.

Having vibrant colors in your outfits can have extreme dopamine dressing effects. But, your seasonal outfit selections don’t need to be all gray and black.

It can be hard to add colorful items to your wardrobe due to the constant fear that you will have nothing to wear them with. The good news is, that pops of color are trending and they don't have to be the same color or shade to match. You can wear a green jacket with silver shoes and call it fashion. That makes it easy on you if you have a lot of basic pieces in your closet to spice things up with a simple pop of color.

DETERMINE COLORS THAT COMPLEMENT YOUR SKIN TONE
Our skin has undertones that must be considered when we start adding color. The wrong colors can wash you out or highlight the color blotches and variations in your skin.

So, when adding a pop of color, determine a color range that will look good on your skin tone. It can be frustrating when you find a piece you love, try it on, and it just doesn’t look as good on you as it does the model and you don’t know why. It might be the wrong color for you. Keep your selections within your ideal color spectrum.

ALWAYS CONSIDER THE COLOR WHEEL 
If you’re just adding one color, styling is really easy. Any color can pair with an otherwise neutral ensemble. But, when you add multiple colors, things get a little more complicated. To find colors that complement each other, simply grab tones that are on the opposite end of the color wheel.

PICK A COLOR GROUP THAT EXCITES YOU
Neon, pastel, metallic, primary - there are so many color groups to choose from. Pick a color group that suits your skin’s undertone, but pick a color group that excites you too! If it makes you happy, you’ll wear it with more confidence, and that’ll naturally make your look more flattering.

STYLE MISTAKES

You can effortlessly look stylish and feel your best if you avoid common style mistakes most people make. Many women and men ignore simple fashion basics and miss out on easy techniques to improve their dressing style.

Here are some of the most common fashion mistakes you need to stop making right now to dress well and showcase your best features instantly.

FORGETTING ABOUT THE SILHOUETTE & PROPORTIONS
Never forget about the silhouette that works for your body type. What looks good on someone else, doesn't mean it looks good on you.Clothing doesn’t look the same on different body types.

WRINKLED CLOTHES
Like wrinkles on the skin show signs of age, fabric wrinkles make the clothing look older, worn out, and off-trend even it's a new piece.

WEARING THE WRONG COLORS
Wearing the wrong colors for you can ruin your look instantly. Instead, choose the right combination of colors that suits your skin tone best. Wearing the wrong color for your skin tone can make you look either pale or even bigger.

MIXING THE WRONG COLORS & TEXTURES WITH EACH OTHER
Combining 2 or more wrong colors and textures with each other can destroy the whole look. You should always think of cold and warm color tones working together, and thick and thin fabrics for clothes/shoes.

NEGLECTING LAYERS
Don't neglect layers when you put together your outfits. Pick a handful of attractive layers that you can add to your daily looks. Overcoats, blazers, gilets, parkas, puffers, vests, and liners help you stand out and transform casual clothing into timeless and elegant outfits.

CHOOSING QUANTITY OVER QUALITY
When it comes to your wardrobe, don't choose quantity over quality. Don't excessively buy fast fashion, disposable, and cheaply made clothing.
Instead, choose more durable and high-quality pieces that look beautiful, last longer, and make you feel your best.

SKIPPING THE TAILOR
It may seem like a no-brainer, but your tailor should really be one of your best fashion friends. Because you can't deny the power of a perfect-fitting outfit. Short/long hemline, short sleeves, loose waist, etc. can make your outfit lost and not flattering at all.

5 KEYS TO ELEVATE YOUR STYLE

Elevating your style is extremely simple. However, looking stylish and put together doesn't always mean wearing the latest trends. Nor does it mean spending money on designer brands. In fact, a lot of it comes not from what you own but what you do. Here’s where you can start if you want to elevate your look.

KNOW YOUR STYLE
People who have amazing style are always confident in their look. They know what works and what doesn’t and essentially what makes their look their own. If you’re still a little unsure of your style, pay attention to things that you always gravitate towards. Pinpoint the pieces that make you feel and look amazing. You’ll soon be able to distill what it is that defines your aesthetic.

MAKE SURE YOU HAVE THE BASICS
It’s important to make sure you’ve got the basics covered before you can evolve your style to the next level. This means everything from having a go-to blazer to having the right underwear for various silhouettes and casual staples like t-shirts and jeans. Having reliable pieces already sitting in your closet will allow you to concentrate on how you can give those things your own unique spin.

HAVE A TAILOR THAT YOU TRUST
There’s something quite special about having a wardrobe filled with pieces that are perfectly fitted to your body - clothes just sit better when they’re tailored.

INVEST IN QUALITY ITEMS
There are workhorses in every wardrobe and they need to be the best quality that you can afford. Quality items generally withstand wear and tear a little better.

DRESS FOR YOUR BODY TYPE
Learning to dress for your body type is a life-changing moment. You look far more polished and elegant when you're wearing clothes that work together to flatter the specific body type you have.

FASHION TIPS TO ENSURE YOU ALWAYS LOOK POLISHED

People underestimate the power of fashion. But defining your style and developing a unique outfit is one of the most effective communication tools. Become your own master stylist with a few reliable tips I'm going to share with you.

1. WORK ON YOUR BASE and CAPSULE WARDROBE
Make sure you have reliable wardrobe staples - an iconic black dress, a pair of jeans that fit perfectly, a classic blazer, simple T-shirts and button-downs in neutral colors, etc. Investing in a capsule collection of mix-and-match basics (and learning how to style them) is the key to looking put together.

2. MAKE SURE YOUR CLOTHES FIT PERFECTLY
One trick to making any item of clothing look amazing is to hire a good stylist who'll put everything together for you and a tailor. Tailored clothing don’t only look polished, but it also feels more comfortable.

3. LEARN HOW TO BALANCE PROPORTIONS
Balancing proportions is about styling your outfits to create an overall aesthetic harmony. Always pay attention to sleeve and pant/skirt length, shoulder and waist line, etc. Because any small misbalance in proportions can make you look shorter, wider, and can change the look of your body type completely.

4. FIND YOUR PERSONAL STYLE
Developing a signature style can take years. Remember that personal style is an experiment. You never know what amazing looks await you until you're in the fitting room. The categories "menswear" and "womenswear" shouldn't dictate how you shop. Take time to play with colors and shapes to find what looks great on your unique body.

5.MIX PATTERNS & TEXTURES
The days of matching your handbag to your shoes are over. Clashing textures and prints make a bold fashion statement. Start small with neutral patterns like stripes and low-key textures like leather and knits, adding in the sequins and patterns in small amounts until you learn what works for you.

In case you don’t feel like stepping out of your usual style, but you still want to add a few changes, start with mixing contrasting colors. Just make sure colors are different from each other but still in a same undertones (warm or cool).

Keep it cool by pairing some unexpected pieces together. The secret to dressy casual is balancing the fancier pieces with more laidback items and accessories.

Mixing styles doesn’t have to be hard, but it’s important to emphasize the importance of keeping the fine balance between stylish and extreme.
